parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause distractions while driving, leading to accidents or near-misses. The system's random behavior can also cause frustration and anxiety for the driver.
symptoms: without user input; the screen is unresponsive or freezes; the system mutes or unmutes Bluetooth calls; the system switches radio stations or skips tracks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear view camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, especially in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The rear view camera display is distorted
or black; the camera system fails to engage or disengage properly; the system malfunctions when the trunk is opened or closed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiper system can reduce visibility while driving in rainy or snowy conditions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers fail to operate or operate intermittently; the wipers stop working during heavy rain or snow; the system malfunctions due to a faulty relay or other electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including stalling, loss of power, or electrical shocks, which can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving; the battery dies repeatedly; the electrical system malfunctions
causing warning lights or error codes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Front Body Power Module can cause the windshield wipers to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially during heavy rain or snow.
symptoms: wipers leave a film on the windshield
wipers stop working in auto rain detection mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the rear backup camera wiring can cause the camera to malfunction, reducing the driver's visibility and increasing the risk of accidents when reversing.
A defective sunroof can cause it to crack or shatter without warning, potentially causing injury or distraction to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Sunroof cracks or shatters without warning
bubbled up glass on the sunroof.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation in the trunk can lead to rusting, mold, and damage to the spare tire and other components, compromising the vehicle's overall safety and performance.
symptoms: with no apparent source or cause.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning rearview camera can increase the risk of accidents, particularly when reversing, as it is an essential safety feature.
symptoms: The rearview camera display is black
or the camera fails to work altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty speed sensor can trigger multiple warning lights, including traction control, ABS, emergency brake, and tire pressure indicator, which can distract the driver and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Multiple warning lights on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A shattered sunroof can cause injuries, damage to the vehicle's interior, and compromise the overall safety of the occupants.
symptoms: without any apparent cause or warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Potential Vehicle Defect Contributing to Fatal Accident
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A potential vehicle defect may have contributed to a fatal accident, highlighting the importance of thorough investigations and recalls.
symptoms: The vehicle veered or crossed the double yellow line before impact
but the exact cause of the accident is unclear.
